<barrons:question>
<![CDATA[<TextFlow xmlns="http://ns.adobe.com/textLayout/2008">
<p>If <span fontStyle="italic">A</span> is the point (&#8722;4, 1) and <span fontStyle="italic">B</span> is the point (2, 1), what is the area of the circle that has <span fontStyle="italic">AB</span> as a diameter?</p>
</TextFlow>]]>
</barrons:question>

<barrons:choices layout="bottom">
<barrons:choice correct="false"><![CDATA[<TextFlow xmlns="http://ns.adobe.com/textLayout/2008"><p>  3π</p></TextFlow>]]></barrons:choice>
<barrons:choice correct="false"><![CDATA[<TextFlow xmlns="http://ns.adobe.com/textLayout/2008"><p>  6π</p></TextFlow>]]></barrons:choice>
<barrons:choice correct="true"><![CDATA[<TextFlow xmlns="http://ns.adobe.com/textLayout/2008"><p>  9π</p></TextFlow>]]></barrons:choice>
<barrons:choice correct="false"><![CDATA[<TextFlow xmlns="http://ns.adobe.com/textLayout/2008"><p>12π</p></TextFlow>]]></barrons:choice>
<barrons:choice correct="false"><![CDATA[<TextFlow xmlns="http://ns.adobe.com/textLayout/2008"><p>36π</p></TextFlow>]]></barrons:choice>
</barrons:choices>

<barrons:explanation>
<![CDATA[<TextFlow xmlns="http://ns.adobe.com/textLayout/2008">
<p><span fontWeight="bold">9π</span></p>
<p>Draw a diagram. Since the distance between (&#8722;4, 1) and (2, 1) is 6, the diameter of the circle is 6 and the radius is 3. Then the area is π(3)<span baselineShift="superscript">2</span> = 9π.</p>
